   :wanted "an ArSE write happens IFF :type ∈ {:query :answer}; the other five performatives stay ambient
            — the Evidence ⊇ ArSE ⊋ ambient boundary as a dispatch invariant, not a doc paragraph (TB-4)"
   :discharged-by "b4ed15f (maybe-typed-bell-arse-bridge! case: only :query/:answer write; default inert)"}
  {:at :ref-in-reply-to-fidelity+idempotent
   :wanted "a :query stamps the job :ref with the new ArSE thread-id; the matching :answer posts with
            in-reply-to == :ref (TB-5); replay of a bell reuses the job BEFORE the bridge runs → no second
            thread (TB-7)"
   :discharged-by "b4ed15f (bridge stamps :ref via ref'; existing-job 202 reused-branch precedes the bridge)"}
  {:at :crossing-soundness
   :wanted "any crossing remaining in graph has NO :answer-with-:ref linking the two directions; typed
            replies are never reported as crossings — only genuine both-asking cases survive (TB-6)"
   :discharged-by "b4ed15f (bell_router/graph reply-of treats :answer whose :ref ∈ bell-ids as a reply)"}
  {:at :send-time-write-speech-act-is-the-send
   :wanted "the ArSE write fires at SEND-time in handle-bell, not at the recipient's drain — asking is asking
            regardless of whether B answers; an unanswered :query is a legible durable gap (D5)"
   :discharged-by "b4ed15f (bridge called in handle-bell before create-invoke-job!, off the concurrency drain path)"}
  {:at :real-asks-not-mislabeled-synthetic
   :wanted "genuine agent/human :query bells must NOT be filed as generated seed data (:synthetic true) —
            latent, but corrupts S4's synthetic-keyed work-queue"
